# Environment Configuration

## Development Environment

Create a `.env.local` file in the project root with the following variables:

```env
# API Configuration
VITE_API_URL=http://localhost:3001/api

# Optional: Google Maps API Key (for map integration)
VITE_GOOGLE_MAPS_KEY=your_google_maps_key_here

# Optional: Firebase Configuration (for notifications)
VITE_FIREBASE_API_KEY=your_firebase_key_here
VITE_FIREBASE_PROJECT_ID=your_project_id

# Optional: Analytics
VITE_ANALYTICS_ID=your_analytics_id

# Optional: Feature Flags
VITE_ENABLE_BETA_FEATURES=false
VITE_ENABLE_OFFLINE_MODE=false
```

## Production Environment

For production builds, set these environment variables:

```env
VITE_API_URL=https://api.tirthecho.com/api
VITE_GOOGLE_MAPS_KEY=prod_google_maps_key
VITE_FIREBASE_API_KEY=prod_firebase_key
VITE_FIREBASE_PROJECT_ID=prod_project_id
VITE_ANALYTICS_ID=prod_analytics_id
VITE_ENABLE_BETA_FEATURES=false
VITE_ENABLE_OFFLINE_MODE=true
```

## Notes

- Never commit `.env.local` to version control
- Keep sensitive keys secure
- Use different keys for development and production
- Update API URL based on deployment environment
